olive oil
2 potato
2 courgette
1 tomato
1 radish
1 tbs plain flour
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into wedges.
• Place wedges on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, trim and cut courgette lengthways
into 2cm-thin sticks. Roughly chop tomato.
Thinly slice radish.

• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and a
pinch of salt.
• In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg.
• In a third shallow bowl, combine panko
breadcrumbs, Aussie spice blend and
grated Parmesan cheese.
• Coat courgette slices in the flour, followed
by the egg and finally the panko-Parmesan
mixture. Transfer to a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with
enough olive oil to cover the base. Cook
crumbed courgette in batches, until golden and
cooked through, 2-3 minutes each side.
• Transfer to a second lined oven tray and bake
until golden, 10-15 minutes.

• While the courgette is baking, combine
mixed salad leaves, tomato, radish and a
drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil.
Season to taste.

• Divide cheesy crumbed courgette, potato
wedges and radish salad between plates.
• Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!